title: Millburn High School varsity girls soccer team posts pair of 1-0 wins
text:
Millburn High School varsity girls soccer team posts pair of 1-0 wins October 15, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 15, 2015, 10:17 AM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills Buy this photo photo courtesy of lynne dembner Millburn High School's Emma Hou (black headband) celebrates with teammates Kelsea Brown (24), Anna Sophia Roberts (12) and Catherine O'Neill Oct. 12 after giving the Millers a 1-0 lead in the first half against visiting West Essex High School. 
A pair of 1-0 home victories allowed the Millburn High School varsity girls soccer team to record back-to-back wins for the first time this season. 
Senior Faith Belcuore scored in the second half off a feed from her sister, Ava, Oct. 8 to give the Millers a 1-0 Senior Night victory over Super Essex Conference, American Division rival Caldwell High School. Ava Belcuore is a sophomore. 
The victory snapped an 0-6-1 winless skid. 
Miller sophomore keeper Katherine Kuiken was credited with 14 saves. 
Freshman Emma Hou converted a first-half pass from senior Lauren O'Neill Oct. 12, lifting the Millers past division rival West Essex High School. 
Kuiken recorded her second consecutive shutout with a 14-save outing. 
Millburn carried an overall record of 4-6-2, 3-6-2 in the American Division, into its Oct. 14 match under the lights at division rival Livingston High School. 
The Lancers won the season's first meeting with the Millers 4-1 Sept. 26 at Millburn High School's Dr. Keith A. Neigel Field. 
-Jim Connelly
